`IFormFile` buffers into memory by default — for large files you need to read the raw request body stream and write to disk in chunks.

**Key changes:**

1. **Disable the form body size limit** and read from `Request.Body` (or use `Request.ReadFormAsync` with `MultipartBodyLengthLimit`).
2. **Stream to disk with a small buffer** instead of materializing the whole file.

```csharp
// Program.cs
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Http.Features;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.WebUtilities;
using Microsoft.Net.Http.Headers;

var builder = WebApplication.CreateBuilder(args);

// Raise Kestrel's max request body size (default is ~28 MB)
builder.WebHost.ConfigureKestrel(o =>
    o.Limits.MaxRequestBodySize = 2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024); // 2 GB

var app = builder.Build();

app.MapPost("/upload", async (HttpRequest request) =>
{
    // Verify it's a multipart request
    if (!request.HasFormContentType ||
        !MediaTypeHeaderValue.TryParse(request.ContentType, out var mt) ||
        !mt.MediaType.Equals("multipart/form-data", StringComparison.OrdinalIgnoreCase))
    {
        return Results.BadRequest("Expected multipart/form-data");
    }

    var boundary = HeaderUtilities.RemoveQuotes(mt.Boundary).Value;
    var reader   = new MultipartReader(boundary, request.Body);

    MultipartSection? section;
    while ((section = await reader.ReadNextSectionAsync()) != null)
    {
        if (!ContentDispositionHeaderValue.TryParse(section.ContentDisposition, out var cd)
            || !cd.IsFileDisposition())
            continue;

        // Sanitize the file name
        var fileName = Path.GetRandomFileName() + Path.GetExtension(cd.FileName.Value);
        var savePath = Path.Combine("/tmp/uploads", fileName);

        // Stream directly to disk — only the buffer is in memory
        await using var fs = new FileStream(savePath, FileMode.Create);
        await section.Body.CopyToAsync(fs);          // default 80 KB buffer
    }

    return Results.Ok("Upload complete");
})
.DisableAntiforgery();   // needed for minimal-API form posts without AF token

app.Run();
```

**Why this works:**

| | `IFormFile` | `MultipartReader` |
|---|---|---|
| Memory | Entire file buffered | Only an 80 KB copy-buffer |
| 2 GB file | OOM / crash | Streams fine |
| Reads body | After model binding | Chunk-by-chunk, on demand |

**Don't forget:**

- **Kestrel limit** — `MaxRequestBodySize` defaults to ~28 MB; set it to `2L * 1024 * 1024 * 1024`.
- **If behind IIS/Nginx** — also raise `maxAllowedContentLength` (IIS `web.config`) or `client_max_body_size` (Nginx).
- **Don't use `[FromForm]`** — any model-binding attribute will buffer the body before your code runs.
- **Validate early** — check `Content-Length`, file extension, and consider hashing chunks for integrity.
